/*This program collects five 2-digit test scores from the LC3 console (from the user input.) It then stores each test in an array and outputs the array in the LC3 console. The program then calculates the maximum, minimum and average of the five test scores and displays the result onto the LC3 console.*/
The size of an array is set to SIZE = 5
if SIZE > 0 then				//BRz or BRn, INLOOP Starts
{
for( SIZE = 1 to 5)
	{
Print out message “Input test score:”
	user inputs -> characterOne 
	if (characterOne !=0)
{
	characterOne is converted from ASCII to a decimal value by taking characterOne + (-16) +(-16) +(-16)
	integerOne = characterOne is now equivalent to an integer 
	tenthsDigit = integerOne*10
} 
	Else
{
characterOne = 0
integerOne =  0
tenthsDigit = 0
}
Print out message “Input test score:”
characterTwo is converted from ASCII to a decimal value by taking characterTwo + (-16) +(-16) +(-16)
integerTwo = characterTwo is now equivalent to an integer
onesDigit = integerTwo
score = tenthsDigit + onesDigit
Store the score into SIZE-1 index of the array (ARRAY[SIZE-1])
Decrease the SIZE by 1 (--SIZE)
for(values in array addresses x3140 to x3144 o)
{
tensValue = score / 10
onesValue = score % 10
outputScore = tensValue,onesValue 
/*since we can only work with one digit at a time you just output each digit side by side*/
Output <-outputScore
}
// The value of X that is first used is the first score that was entered
Take a value from the array and subtract a selected value of 0 for Y 
//for loop that finds the max score
for(values in array addresses x3140 to x3144)
{
Increment base case address by 1 
Load the value at that address to the address for X
Then operate X-Y

if(X-Y < 0) //BRn NEGMAX
{
The maximum is Y and stores into the address of Y						
else if (X-Y >  0)
{
The maximum is X and the value gets passed to Y and stored into the address of Y
}
Else
There is no difference and both numbers are the maximum the value of X gets passed and stored into the address of Y
	}

Take the value at the base case from the array and subtract the last maximum value 
//for loop that finds the min score

for(values in array addresses x3140 to x3144)
{
if (X-Y < 0) 
{
The minimum is X and the value of X gets passed to Y and stores into the address of Y						
else if (X-Y > 0)
{
The minimum is Y and the value gets stored into the address of Y
}
Else
There is no difference and both numbers are the minimum and the value of X gets passed to Y and stored into the address of Y
	}
Increment base case address by 1 
Load the value at that address to the address for X
Then operate X-Y

	}
		


			
									
EXIT

















